163. le. xxii. 10. Used after the battle at the lacus Trasimennus 537l217. The ver sacrum was an ancient Italic custom. It was vowed when the state was in extreme peril: all the young animals born in a particular season were sacrificed. There are indioetions that in remote antiquity even the children born shared the same fate. The above is not exactly the form of the vow itself, but the proposal made to the comitia.
